  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Transition Manager",
  "description": "<p>We’re looking for a Transition Manager to lead the smooth onboarding and transition of IT services into steady-state operations. You’ll work closely with clients, delivery teams, and vendors to ensure seamless service takeovers with minimal disruption.</p><p>This is a hands-on, delivery-focused role, ideal for professionals with strong transition, ITSM, or project coordination experience.<br /></p><p><strong>Responsibilities :</strong></p><ul><li>Manage end-to-end service transitions across people, process, and technology</li><li>Develop and execute transition plans, timelines, and risk registers</li><li>Coordinate knowledge transfer, documentation, and operational readiness</li><li>Act as the key transition point of contact for clients and internal teams</li><li>Support go-live and hypercare to ensure service stability</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements :</strong></p><ul><li>7–10 years of total workplace experience</li><li><p>4+ years in service transition, project management, or IT operations</p></li><li><p>Strong understanding of ITIL / IT Service Management</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in IT services, managed services, or outsourcing environments</p></li><li><p>Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills</p></li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 7,
